# ClearAI Frontend — environment variables
#
# After the BFF cutover (docs/SECURITY-REMEDIATION-PLAN.md §1), the SPA
# bundle holds NO secrets. Every API call goes through the same-origin
# /api/* path served by clearai-frontend/api/ (the SWA managed-function
# BFF), which holds the Entra client_secret + APIM details server-side.
#
# What used to be here (REMOVED — see frontend security review C1, H1):
#   PUBLIC_CLEARAI_API_BASE=https://apim-...    # bundled into JS — dropped
#   PUBLIC_CLEARAI_API_KEY=<32-char-hex>        # APIM subscription key — DROPPED, was the C1 critical
#
# Build-time vars (PUBLIC_*) below are NOT secrets — they get inlined into
# the bundle. Only put public, non-credential strings here. Real secrets
# live in clearai-frontend/api/local.settings.json (gitignored) for local
# dev, and in SWA Application Settings (Configuration blade) for prod.

# Optional dev escape hatch — point /api at a non-same-origin BFF (e.g. a
# remote preview slot). Default empty = relative same-origin which is what
# both production and local-with-`func start`-on-7071 want (since SWA's
# `swa start` proxies /api → :7071 transparently).
# PUBLIC_CLEARAI_DEV_API_PROXY=
